parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Foggy Substance Between Double Panel Window Glass
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The foggy substance between the double panel window glass can obstruct the driver's view, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when changing lanes or merging with traffic.
symptoms: A foggy or hazy substance appears between the double panel window glass
making it difficult to see outside
which can interfere with the rearview mirror; the windshield is the only clear glass.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fogging of windows, particularly the driver-side window, can significantly impair visibility, making it hazardous to drive, especially when changing lanes or passing. This can lead to accidents and pose a risk to the driver and other road users.
symptoms: making it difficult to see the left side mirror
or other areas of the road; defrost function does not operate normally; sealant on windows fails to seal them properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the refrigerator cooling unit can lead to the leakage of coolant gas (ammonia) into the coach, causing occupants to become ill and lightheaded. This can also create a fire hazard if the gas ignites, potentially causing damage to the coach.
symptoms: Coolant gas leakage into the coach
risk of fire or uncontrolled ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the slider mechanism can cause the slider to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to operate, which can compromise the safety of the occupants, especially when traveling alone.
symptoms: Slider fails to retract or close properly
requires multiple people to lift and push to close
fear of being stuck in a location without mechanical help

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Improper Installation of Slide Out Seals
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The improper installation of slide out seals can lead to water leaks and damage to the interior of the motor home, compromising the structural integrity of the vehicle and creating an unsafe environment for occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Multiple Safety-Related Issues in Motor Homes
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The combination of multiple safety-related issues can increase the risk of accidents, injuries, and fatalities, as well as compromise the overall safety and reliability of the motor home.
